Folder Structure

Place the downloaded files in the following directory:


Retinal_project/
│
├── dataset/
│   ├── ODIR.zip
│   ├── aptos.zip
│   └── Idrid.zip
│
├── checkpoints/
│   ├── ckpt_clip_full.pth
│   ├── ckpt_clip_linear.pth
│   ├── ckpt_clip_lora.pth
│   ├── ckpt_dinov2_full.pth
│   ├── ckpt_dinov2_linear.pth
│   ├── ckpt_dinov2_lora.pth
│   ├── ckpt_vit_full.pth
│   ├── ckpt_vit_linear.pth
│   └── ckpt_vit_lora.pth
│
├── figures/
│
├── results/
│
└── retinal_foundation_models.ipynb

----------------------------------------------------

Running the Project

1. Mount Google Drive in Google Colab.
2. Place the datasets and checkpoints in the structure shown above.
3. Open retinal_foundation_models.ipynb.
4. Run all cells.

If checkpoints are available, the notebook loads them automatically.
Otherwise, it starts training the models from scratch.
